    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-07T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-07T08:00:00-05:00" n="715"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d715">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.00B <persName>Rubens, Adolph A.</persName>/44:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_GSE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grummon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-07T16:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 7, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 7—12:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>294. Department’s telegram No. 40, April 15, 3 p.m. I have just been informed by
                    telephone by <persName corresp="#p_RAA1">Rosh</persName>, the Acting Chief of
                    the Third Western Division of the Commissariat for Foreign Affairs, that the
                    Commissariat has been apprised by the competent Soviet authorities that a
                    judgment will be rendered in the Rubens case shortly. I requested information as
                    to the place and date of trial and permission to be present thereat and have
                    confirmed this request in writing. In response to an inquiry regarding Mrs.
                        <persName>Rubens</persName>’ welfare <persName corresp="#p_RAA1"
                        >Rosh</persName> asserted that he was without information. When I asked
                    regarding her whereabouts he stated “I think she is in Moscow but I am not
                    certain.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grummon</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
